# Environment

{{#if isNextJS}}
- Expose browser-safe variables with `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` only.
{{/if}}
{{#if isNuxt}}
- Use `runtimeConfig` for server vs public values; document which keys are client-visible.
{{/if}}
{{#if isAngular}}
- Use `environment.ts` files per build configuration; never commit secrets.
{{/if}}
{{#if isSvelteKit}}
- Use SvelteKit modules (`$env/static/public`, etc.) for public vs private env; never leak server keys to the client bundle.
{{/if}}
{{#if isRemix}}
- Follow Remix + Vite env patterns; only expose what loaders/actions need; document server-only variables.
{{/if}}
{{#if isAstro}}
- Use `import.meta.env` with `PUBLIC_*` prefix for client-visible Astro variables.
{{/if}}
{{#if (and (eq metaFramework "none") (or isReact isVue isSvelte isSolid isPreact))}}
- For Vite-based SPA stacks, use `VITE_*` prefixes for client-exposed values.
{{/if}}

## Files

- Commit `.env.example` with dummy values; **never** commit real `.env` files.

## Validation

- Validate env at startup (Zod / framework helpers) to fail fast in CI and production.

## Feature flags

- Evaluate flags at stable boundaries (layout, route guard, provider) — not inside every leaf component.
